What do you want to happen in auto? Be very specific. You said “it suppose to drive forward shoot the ball out and go back”. This leaves many questions: Drive forward how far or how long? Drive forward at what speed? What do you mean by shoot? I see an arm and an intake. Do you use your intake to shoot also? How long should is “shoot”? How long/far should it drive back? How fast should it drive back?

Let’s separate and clearly identify what problems you are having. Which auto are you running is it just the default? Why have you gone away from the premade templates that are given to you? Those templates are there to make this process easy and doing it yourself like this can easily run into pitfalls if you don’t know what you are doing.

For the teleop problem which joystick is working and which is not? What is it doing? Is it properly identified and in the right slot on the Driver station?

If you don’t have anyone more experienced to help you with this it is probably needed to do a zoom call with someone so they can see / help with all of the different issues.

Have you seen the documentation here?

Which of your two autonomous routines are you wanting to run?

One looks like it’s trying to shoot the intake for a while but likely won’t succeed due to the enable being on.

The other looks like it’s trying to read joystick outputs in autonomous so I wouldn’t expect it to work as you desire either.

Let’s start with jdaming’s questions. Talk through step by step exactly what you want to happen. From there, we can look at helping you get that into code.

Driving for 5-10 seconds at 50 percent power will take you a long way. You probably don’t want it going that long but you can test it.

Does it take your shooter 5-10 seconds to shoot 1 ball?

Auto only lasts for 15 seconds so you need to fit all of these steps into that time[Autonomous Independent.

So you are saying that your joysticks will not work intermittently? But they both will work occasionally? This seems like a hardware / configuration problem. Before you go to enable are you checking the joysticks using the 4th tab on the driver station?

I have attached an Auto that I believe does what you want in “Alternative 2”.

Autonomous Independent jdaming.zip (39.6 KB)
